  "title": {
    "rendered": "Experiment: glass"
  },
  "content": {
    "rendered": "<p>One of the nicest emergent behaviours I know is recursion. For this experiment a screenshot is taken and placed at a different angle, offset and scale. Then repeated indefinitely. For colouring I added a really light gradient each cycle (otherwise the image would recurse into a single colour).<br />\nThe result looks mostly fractal.</p>\n<p><!--more--></p>\n<p>Click it!</p>\n<pre><code data-language=\"javascript\" data-src=\"/wordpress/wp-content/themes/sjeiti/static/experiment/glass.js\"></code></pre>\n",
    "protected": false
  },
  "excerpt": {
    "rendered": "<p>One of the nicest emergent behaviours I know is recursion. For this experiment a screenshot is taken and placed at a different angle, offset and scale. Then repeated indefinitely. For colouring I added a really light gradient each cycle (otherwise the image would recurse into a single colour). The result looks mostly fractal.</p>\n",
    "protected": false
  },
